Composition
===========
	---->lti a---->lti b------>
	h=a*b=b*a

	Or just find frequency response and multiply.

Impulse Response to Frequency Response
======================================
	e^(iwn)--->LTI--->H(w)e^(iwn)
	(h*x)(n)=\sum_(k=-\inf)^(\inf) k(k)x(n-k)
	=\sum h(k) e^((iw)(n-k))

	H(w)=\sum_(k=-\inf)^(\inf) h(k)e^(-iwk)

Filtering
=========
	Simplest Low Pass Filter
	------------------------
		y(n)=1/L \sum_(k=0)^(L-1) x(n-k)

		Averages over the last L samples

		h(k)={1/L, 0<=k<=L-1; 0 otherwise}

		H(w)=(1/3)\sum_(k=0)^(L-1) e^(-iwk), a geometric series: sum a^k=(1-a^k)/(1-a)
		=(1/L)((1-e^(iwL))/(1-e(-iw)))
	
	Simple High Pass Filtering
	--------------------------
		y(n)=(1/2)(x(n)-x(n-1))
		Derivative filters out low frequencies
